-- Hungary Banks See $940 Million Loss on Loan Plan, Portfolio Says
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2012-02-02T14:23:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-02/hungary-banks-see-940-million-loss-on-loan-plan-portfolio-says.html
Hungarian commercial banks forecast a
loss of 210 billion forint ($940 million) from a government plan
allowing the repayment of foreign-currency mortgages at below-
market rates, news website  Portfolio  said, citing Mihaly Patai,
head of the Bank Association.  Lenders booked losses of 143 billion forint on repayments
through mid-January and this figure will swell further as the
plan runs until the end of February, Portfolio cited Patai as
saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
